summary: that one time i saw dan and phil but was too young to realise
body:
that one time i saw dan and phil but was too young to realise

okay so i was talking with my mum recently, and she was telling me a story about one vacation we went on that had a seemingly unreal part.


the thing is, is that as a british family living in the u.s, we don’t usually find other English people just walking around. until we decided to go on a vacation to Universal Studios. i was young, but old enough to remember this (‘‘twas about 6 years ago)


i was standing in line with my family, chatting my head off in my loud accent when i shut up for a minute and hear fateful words. another english accent. two to be exact. you’re probably wondering where im going with this. i turned around, poked my mum and said.


“look at those two guys over there with the accents just like ours mum!” i said and she smiled at me, nodding. i only briefly saw their faces but by gosh dang golly do i remember their hair. two perfect emo fringes of these tall men that abso-frickin-lutely towered over me with a camera in one of their hands and a smile on both of their faces.


so that is the time I saw dan and phil but didn’t even realise it was them because, alas, I was too young, and hadn’t seen any of their videos.


the funniest thing is that as my mum was telling me this story and I was remembering, she finished it off with “so yeah they looked like the two you saw on tour like a month ago.”


thanks mum

@danielhowell @amazingphil
